data.description: WOW - the home you have been looking for! NO HOA - Bring your boat, park your RV, and enjoy life in this small lakefront neighborhood. From your front yard, you have a view of Lake Harris, one of the Chain of Lakes - offering wonderful boating & fishing. This low maintenance home sits on a .43 acre lot. Pride of ownership shows throughout.  2021 Updates include: NEW CABINETS AND GRANITE COUNTERTOPS, NEW STAINLESS APPLIANCES, NEW MASTER BATHROOM, NEW EXTERIOR AND INTERIOR PAINT, FRONT ENTRY WITH STONE ACCENTS, NEW ELECTRICAL PANEL and NEW WATER HEATER. This open floor plan features a large living room with wood-burning fireplace. The kitchen offers an abundance of cabinets and counterspace.  You'll enjoy entertaining in the spacious Dining Room featuring a rock accent wall with wood-burning stove. The party continues on the back screened-in porch with your own Tiki bar where family and friends gather outdoors for cookouts, celebrations, and weekend get togethers. Or enjoy the sunset over the lake from your 31'x17' screened-in front porch.  The split bedroom floorplan features two bedrooms, a bathroom with tub and shower on one side, the master bedroom on the other side. The Owner's Suite is a private sanctuary offering a master bedroom plus an additional room for a nursery, office, or TV room.  The newly remodeled ensuite bathroom features an oversized soaking tub as well as a walk-in shower.  This property is the perfect combination of small town living with big city access. You'll be surprised by how close you are to restaurants, shopping, grocery stores, public boat ramp, and more. Boating enthusiasts will love exploring the Harris Chain of Lakes, utilizing the public boat ramp just minutes away. The quaint towns of Mount Dora, Tavares & The Villages are also a short drive away for year-round festivals & waterfront dining. Enjoy all Central Florida has to offer when visiting property. Sellers have an Assumable FHA Loan.
